$$ \Delta T=\frac{\Delta \mathrm{ln}({\rm{CO}}_{2})}{\mathrm{ln}(2)}\times \frac{s*}{(1-{f}_{1})(1-{f}_{2})}.$$
\end{document}

The values of the parameters discussed in 10.1007/978-94-007-4988-7_4 were as follows: s*  =  1.5°C to s*  =  5.5°C, which are taken from climate models rather than based on the historical value s*  =  1.2°C; f
1  =  0.20 to f
1  =  0.73; and f
2  =  0.042 to f
2  =  0.067. Weitzman argues that the subsequent scaling multiplier, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
